{"sequence":17,"timestamp":"2026-04-04T23:42:03.951645026Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-8ac4d34c","body":"Update `src/test_support/fixtures.rs:87-103`, `src/test_support/fixtures.rs:154-189`, and `src/test_support/fixtures.rs:607-617` so `BeadGraphFixtureBuilder` emits the real `.beads/issues.jsonl` schema instead of the repo’s internal read models. The current helper writes records without required issue metadata (`created_at`, `created_by`, `updated_at`, `source_repo`, `compaction_level`, `original_size`), serializes `acceptance_criteria` as `Vec<String>` instead of the string field that `br` expects, and serializes dependencies as `DependencyRef` objects instead of dependency rows with `issue_id` / `depends_on_id` / `type` metadata. As written, any non-empty bead graph fixture is rejected by the real tooling, so the shared workspace helper does not satisfy the “valid .beads directory structure” acceptance criterion.","dedup_key":"9096a59a725af12866828c9f86fab1e3555d6299cfe62117c2f425578f7062cc","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260404231226","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":18,"timestamp":"2026-04-04T23:42:03.961003790Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-f5f06584","body":"Rework `src/test_support/logging.rs:41-59` and `src/test_support/logging.rs:168-182` so log capture is isolated per test instead of a single process-global sink installed with `set_global_default`. The current API shares one global `Vec<CapturedLogEvent>` across all callers and exposes `clear()`/`snapshot()` on that shared buffer, which means parallel tests can erase or contaminate each other’s events. It also panics if any other test or helper installs a tracing subscriber first. A scoped subscriber/guard or an explicit global serialization mechanism is needed before this can serve as repo-wide shared test infrastructure.","dedup_key":"e351081fac4b500be325730a9e89492d193334123e259dc7538f7c6e39f3eb4f","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260404231226","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
